### ============================================================
### Kids Quiz Backend — API Test File
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension, or copy into Postman
### Run requests in ORDER — each step uses IDs from the previous
### ============================================================

@base = http://localhost:3000/api

### ─── VARIABLES (fill in after each step) ───────────────────
@quiz_id = PASTE_QUIZ_ID_HERE
@attempt_id = PASTE_ATTEMPT_ID_HERE
@question_id = PASTE_QUESTION_ID_HERE
@option_id = PASTE_OPTION_ID_HERE
@user_id = PASTE_USER_ID_HERE


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 0. HEALTH CHECK
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Check server is alive
GET http://localhost:3000


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. USERS — Register a child
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Register a new child user → copy "id" into @user_id above
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Tommy",
  "age": 8
}

###

### Get all users
GET {{base}}/users

###

### Get one user with their quiz history
GET {{base}}/users/{{user_id}}


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. QUIZZES — Create & fetch
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all quizzes (use the seeded one, or create your own below)
GET {{base}}/quizzes

###

### Get quiz details (set @quiz_id first)
GET {{base}}/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}

###

### Create a brand new quiz → copy the returned "id" into @quiz_id
POST {{base}}/quizzes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Space Explorer Quiz",
  "description": "How much do you know about outer space?",
  "category": "science",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "questions": [
    {
      "question_text": "What is the closest star to Earth?",
      "explanation": "The Sun is our nearest star — it gives us light and warmth every day!",
      "options": [
        { "option_text": "The Moon",  "is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "The Sun",   "is_correct": true  },
        { "option_text": "Mars",      "is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "Jupiter",   "is_correct": false }
      ]
    },
    {
      "question_text": "How many planets are in our Solar System?",
      "explanation": "There are 8 planets: Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune.",
      "options": [
        { "option_text": "7",  "is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "8",  "is_correct": true  },
        { "option_text": "9",  "is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "10", "is_correct": false }
      ]
    },
    {
      "question_text": "What do we call a shooting star?",
      "explanation": "Shooting stars are actually meteors — rocks that burn up entering Earth's atmosphere.",
      "options": [
        { "option_text": "Comet",   "is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "Meteor",  "is_correct": true  },
        { "option_text": "Asteroid","is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "Planet",  "is_correct": false }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### Delete a quiz (soft delete)
DELETE {{base}}/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. QUIZ SESSION — The full quiz flow
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### STEP 1: Start the quiz → copy "attempt_id" into @attempt_id
###         Also copy first question "id" into @question_id
###         Also copy one option "id" into @option_id
POST {{base}}/sessions/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quiz_id": "{{quiz_id}}",
  "user_id": "{{user_id}}"
}

###

### STEP 2: Get current session state
GET {{base}}/sessions/{{attempt_id}}

###

### STEP 3: Submit an answer for the current question
###         is_correct / feedback / updated score returned instantly
POST {{base}}/sessions/{{attempt_id}}/answer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question_id": "{{question_id}}",
  "selected_option_id": "{{option_id}}"
}

###

### STEP 4: Move to next question (repeat STEP 3 + STEP 4 for each question)
POST {{base}}/sessions/{{attempt_id}}/next

###

### STEP 5: Go back to previous question (optional)
POST {{base}}/sessions/{{attempt_id}}/prev

###

### STEP 6: Get final results — score, stars, badge, answer review
GET {{base}}/sessions/{{attempt_id}}/results


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 4. PROGRESS — For the frontend progress bar
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get progress data (% complete, remaining questions, score)
GET {{base}}/progress/{{attempt_id}}


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 5. ADMIN — Management & stats
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Overall system stats
GET {{base}}/admin/stats

###

### All quizzes with full question/option data
GET {{base}}/admin/quizzes

###

### All quiz attempts (filter by quiz or completion)
GET {{base}}/admin/attempts

###

### Filter attempts: only completed ones
GET {{base}}/admin/attempts?completed=true

###

### Filter attempts: by specific quiz
GET {{base}}/admin/attempts?quiz_id={{quiz_id}}

###

### Edit a quiz (change title, difficulty, etc)
PUT {{base}}/admin/quizzes/{{quiz_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Quiz Title",
  "difficulty": "hard",
  "is_active": true
}

###

### Edit a question text or explanation
PUT {{base}}/admin/questions/{{question_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question_text": "Updated question text here?",
  "explanation": "Updated explanation here."
}


### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 6. VALIDATION TESTS — These should return 400 errors
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Missing quiz_id → should return 400
POST {{base}}/sessions/start
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Missing answer fields → should return 400
POST {{base}}/sessions/{{attempt_id}}/answer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question_id": "{{question_id}}"
}

###

### Create quiz with no questions → should return 400
POST {{base}}/quizzes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Empty Quiz"
}

###

### Create quiz with question but no correct option → should return 400
POST {{base}}/quizzes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bad Quiz",
  "questions": [
    {
      "question_text": "Which one?",
      "options": [
        { "option_text": "A", "is_correct": false },
        { "option_text": "B", "is_correct": false }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
